150 grams Jasmine Rice
120 grams Peas
1 unit(s) Bell Pepper
240 grams British Beef Mince
150 grams Teriyaki Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle. Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Add the peas for the final 1-2 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, slice the pepper into strips.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.

Once hot, fry the beef mince and pepper, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, stir in the teriyaki sauce. Cook for 1 min more.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's dry.
Fluff up the rice, then share between your bowls.
Top with the stir-fry.
Enjoy!